						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone near Maṭhada hola.</hi></p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">A.D. 1730.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription, the purport of which is not clear is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śāka 1652, Naḷa, Māgha śu. 14.</hi> The date is wrong. <hi rend="italic">Śaka</hi> 1652 coincided with the cyclic year <hi rend="italic">Sādhāraṇa</hi> and the cyclic year <hi rend="italic">Naḷa</hi> coincided with <hi rend="italic">Śaka</hi> 1658. In these two years the given <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1730, February 22, Thursday</hi> and A.D. 1737, February 3, Thursday, respectively.</p>						

						<p>At the top of this stone are engraved some indistinct letters and a certain <hi rend="bold">Marudēva</hi> seems to have been mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
